items.title: How long should it take to get a COVID-19 test result?
items.author: James Maasdorp
items.description: Given you must stay at home until you get your results, you could be forgiven for a little impatience or apprehension while waiting for the call or text message from the health department.

items.title: 'One hell of a thank you': Doctor hit with parking fine says inspectors are targeting hospital staff
items.author: Zalika Rizmal
items.description: A Melbourne doctor takes to social media to question a parking fine she received after working 56 hours over four days in the intensive care ward at the Royal Melbourne Hospital.

items.title: Victorian coronavirus outbreak drives renewed slump in business confidence
items.author: Gareth Hutchens
items.description: Business confidence turns sharply negative again, around the country, amid Victoria's second wave of coronavirus infections.

items.title: Aged care residents continue to dominate Victoria's coronavirus death toll
items.description: Victoria reports 331 new cases of coronavirus and 19 new deaths — the second day in a row Australia's highest daily death toll has been recorded in the state.

items.title: 'Cancel your Christmas plans': NT border controls to remain for at least 18 months
items.author: Lauren Roberts
items.description: Chief Minister Michael Gunner says the Northern Territory is "much more likely" to add more COVID-19 hotspots than to remove any.

items.title: Teddy Sheean panel said it best when it found 'true story was always there'
items.author: Emily Baker
items.description: The story of Edward 'Teddy' Sheean, the WWII sailor who died defending his ship from an attack by the Japanese, is straightforward, his path to a Victoria Cross has been anything but, writes Emily Baker.

items.title: NSW 'on knife edge' as state records highest number of COVID-19 cases in four months
items.description: NSW Premier Gladys Berejiklian says there have been 22 new coronavirus infections in her state, including several fresh cases linked to a school in Sydney's north west.

items.title: Woman dragged from car during 'terrifying' hammer attack in Adelaide

items.title: Sumatrans look on as Mount Sinabung erupts again, sending huge plume of ash into the sky
items.author: Anne Barker
items.description: Mount Sinabung, one of Indonesia's best known volcanos, erupts violently for the second time in three days, sending a giant ash cloud 5 kilometres into the air, turning the sky dark.

items.title: Activist Agnes Chow arrested as China accused of Hong Kong purge
items.author: Bill Birtles
items.description: Well-known activist Agnes Chow is among the latest arrests in Hong Kong under a new national security law, following the high-profile detaining of media owner Jimmy Lai.
